Sentencas: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+delta (PLNCG), a mixed ionic electron conductor (MIEC) with a K2NiF4-type structure, has been studied as a potential cathode material based on YSZ (ZrO2 with 8 mol% Y2O3) electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis reveals that the good chemical compatibility between the PLNCG and YSZ.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum electric conductivity of the PLNCG appeared at about 460 degrees C and the value was 32 S cm(-1) in air and 34 5 cm(-1) in O-2, respectively.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A hollow fiber SOFC was fabricated with the PLNCG as the cathode, NiO-YSZ (1:1; w/w) as the anode and YSZ as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell is 876 mW cm(-2) and the corresponding polarization resistance of the cell is 0.41 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, the PLNCG cathode shows an excellent CO2 resistance in the operation temperature range.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell is similar to that when the cathode is exposed to air.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, the cell performance is stable when the CO2 concentrations in the air vary from 0 to 10 vol.% at both 700 and 750 degrees C. These results indicate that the PLNCG can be a good candidate for CO2 resistance cathode materials of IT-SOFCs based on YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Pr1.8La0.2Ni0.74Cu0.21Ga0.05O4+δ as a potential cathode material with CO2 resistance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
